Marina is a biographical film released in 2013 and directed by Stijn Coninx. 
The film is based upon the life of the Italian singer Rocco Granata who moved 
to Belgium when he was a young boy. It features Matteo Simoni as 
Rocco Granata and Evelien Bosmans as Helena. Most part of the film is in 
Italian as Rocco's parents did not speak the dutch language. 
Other parts are in Dutch and some dialogues in French and English.
